If player has no item in weapon or torso inventory slot.

Said as player passes.

ambient if observed.

This character is positioned on a streetcorner in the docks district. When a charatcer walks by he checks to see if there is an item in the torso slot of the player's inventory, or something in the weapon slot.

He then chooses one of three dialogue lines to pop up, commenting on the worth of the gear, or the lack of any.

He then starts following the player at a distance, turning away if the player gets too close. 

He has an ambient line for DURING following

He has selected dialogue for before he begins following, and for after.

If the player engages in combat, he stays at a distance. If the player leaves the area while he is following, he resets. 

This character is removed when main plot is done.
